    "name": "COU1: Tibial tray contact stress prediction in TKA (Class II)",
    "description": "A finite-element model is used to predict peak contact stress and stress distribution at the tibial tray–bone interface under physiological gait and stair-climb loading for a Class II total knee arthroplasty device. Model influence is MODERATE (model informs but does not solely determine design acceptance; bench testing supplements); decision consequence is MODERATE (design optimisation for implant longevity, not immediate patient safety adjudication). Model Risk Level 3.",
    "intendedUse": "Use FE analysis to predict tibial tray contact stress distributions across three loading scenarios (level gait, stair ascent, stair descent) for a Class II TKA tibial component. Results used to confirm stress levels remain below fatigue endurance limits and to compare design variants. Material uncertainty addressed via Monte Carlo sampling of cortical and cancellous bone moduli.",
